.START 

W. Buck Cody was named president and Orville W. Ehrhardt was named executive vice president of a recently consolidated unit of this machine-tool maker.
The company said the unit, which manufactures machine tools, was created by the combination of its Kearney & Trecker Corp. and Warner & Swasey subsidiaries under the company's previously announced restructuring program.
Cross & Trecker officials said the new unit, which will be based in Milwaukee, currently has no name.
Previously, Mr. Cody, 56 years old, was president of Kearney & Trecker.
Mr. Ehrhardt, 58, was president of Warner & Swasey. 

